href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex>\mathcal {U} \in \mathcal {V}</fr:tex> be an impredicative pair of universes with <fr:tex>A: \mathcal {V}</fr:tex>. There we may construct a  <fr:link
href="jms-003O.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-003O">reflection algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex>A _{ \mathcal {U} }  : { A } \downarrow { \mathcal {U} }</fr:tex> such that for any other <fr:link
href="jms-003O.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-003O">reflection algebra</fr:link> <fr:tex>X: { A } \downarrow { \mathcal {U} }</fr:tex>, the space of <fr:link
href="jms-003O.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-003O">homomorphisms</fr:link> <fr:tex>A _{ \mathcal {U} } \multimap  X</fr:tex> is contractible.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="false"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>14762</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#530</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-530.xml</fr:route><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>3</fr:month><fr:day>22</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-004G</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Our <fr:link
href="jms-0044.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0044">splitting of the generic element of the generic cone</fr:link> <fr:tex>{ \Delta  I } \xrightarrow {{ p }}{ 1 _{ { A } \downarrow { \mathcal {U} } } }</fr:tex> over the identity functor on reflection algebras <fr:link
href="jms-003E.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-003E">yields a new (incoherent) cone</fr:link> <fr:tex>{ \Delta  J } \xrightarrow {{ q }}{ 1 _{ { A } \downarrow { \mathcal {U} } } }</fr:tex> whose generic element <fr:tex>q _{ J } :J \multimap  J</fr:tex> may be identified with the identity homomorphism. It <fr:link
href="jms-003B.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-003B">follows</fr:link> that each  space of homomorphisms <fr:tex>J \to  X</fr:tex> is contractible. Therefore, we define <fr:tex>A _{ \mathcal {U} }</fr:tex> to be the apex <fr:tex>J</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
